Optimizing Gameplay\par
\cf1 -------------------\par
\cf0\par
Be sure to turn off any personal firewall software before attempting to play the game. If you are in fullscreen mode, you may find that the firewall won't give Combat access to the Internet.\par
\par
If you plan to play Combat over the Internet through a connection that uses a permanent firewall, you'll need to contact your network administrator to make sure that you can access port 5088.\par
\par
\cf2 ICQ - If an ICQ popup appears during play, the game may not be able to continue.\par
\par
Motherboard Monitor 5 - Shut down this program on Windows 2000 machines; otherwise, it will cause intermittent slowdowns in gameplay.\par
\par
Zonealarm - Shut down Zonealarm before playing multiplayer games in fullscreen mode; otherwise, Zonealarm may lock up your system.\cf0\par
\par
