\cf0\par
## Special keys ##\par
\par
Shift-O: grabs a screenshot and will place it in your root Combat directory\par
\par
Shift-K: if you really want to take the easy way out, this will destroy your tank.\par
\par
\par
## Goodies ##\par
\par
Be sure to look through the "goodies" folder on the Combat CD. This folder contains some unsupported freebies (unsupported means that technical support isn't available on the software found in the goodies folder--it is "use at your own risk" software).\par
\par
In this folder, you will find the Combat editor that allows you to create your own single or multiplayer map.\par
\par
We have also included the "amo plugin" that allows users who have access to 3D Max to create their own models for the game.\par
\par
You will also find all of the original Combat music in MP3 format.\par
\par
Finally, you will find the Stella Atari 2600 emulator bundled with the original Combat and Combat 2 games for the venerable 2600 home system.\par
\par
All folders contain text files to get you started using these Combat bonus files.\par
\par
\par
## Custom Multiplayer Maps ##\par
\par
If you use the editor to create a custom multiplayer map, heed these rules:\par
*A multiplayer maps does NOT need an Exit\par
*Add as many start points as you want-players will spawn in on a random start location\par
*be sure to name the map "mp*.lvl" with the * being the name you'd like--this way, it'll show up in the MP map list\par
*If you want to have an image of your MP map show up on the list, take a screenshot, reduce it down to 160 x 200 pixels in size. Name it the same as the level name, with a bmp extension, and put it in the \\levels folder under \\textures\par
* when you share a map, you need to give out both the lvl file and the small bitmap (if you created one)\par
